SYN_2_9_3977: PROCEDURE: Rigid bronchoscopy with foreign body retrieval and stent insertion. INDICATION: Malignancy and retained stent. FINDINGS: TBM and bilateral obstruction. ACTION: Diagnostic bronchoscopy performed. Rigid scope utilized. The embedded stent in the left mainstem was liberated using APC and balloon dilation, then extracted. Tumor in the right mainstem was ablated. A customized Y-stent was implanted. CONCLUSION: Airway patency restored.
